  "response_text": "Given the constraints, I'll provide a workout plan and diet that can help you lose 10 lbs without a gym membership and with a limited food budget of $4 per day.\n\n**Workout Plan:**\n\nSince you don't have access to a gym, we'll focus on bodyweight exercises and outdoor activities. Here's a 4-day per week workout plan:\n\n1. Monday (Upper Body):\n\t* Push-ups: 3 sets of 10 reps\n\t* Tricep dips (using a chair or bench): 3 sets of 10 reps\n\t* Arm circles (holding light weights or water bottles): 3 sets of 10 reps\n\t* Plank: 3 sets of 30-second hold\n2. Tuesday (Lower Body):\n\t* Squats: 3 sets of 10 reps\n\t* Calf raises (using bodyweight or a step): 3 sets of 15 reps\n\t* Lunges: 3 sets of 10 reps (per leg)\n\t* Glute bridges: 3 sets of 10 reps\n3. Thursday (Core):\n\t* Russian twists (using a light weight or water bottle): 3 sets of 10 reps\n\t* Leg raises (hanging from a door or bar): 3 sets of 10 reps\n\t* Bicycle crunches: 3 sets of 10 reps\n\t* Wall sit: 3 sets of 30-second hold\n4. Friday (Cardio):\n\t* Brisk walking or jogging: 30 minutes\n\t* Jumping jacks: 3 sets of 30 seconds\n\t* Burpees: 3 sets of 10 reps\n\n**Diet Plan:**\n\nWith a daily food budget of $4, we'll focus on affordable and nutrient-dense foods. Here's a sample meal plan:\n\n* Breakfast: Oatmeal with banana and honey ($1.50)\n\t+ 1 cup rolled oats\n\t+ 1 banana\n\t+ 1 tsp honey\n* Lunch: Peanut butter and jelly sandwich with carrot sticks ($1.50)\n\t+ 2 slices whole wheat bread\n\t+ 2 tbsp peanut butter\n\t+ 2 tbsp jelly\n\t+ 4-5 carrot sticks\n* Snack: Apple slices with almonds ($0.50)\n\t+ 1 medium apple\n\t+ 1 oz almonds\n* Dinner: Black bean and rice bowl ($1.50)\n\t+ 1 cup cooked black beans\n\t+ 1 cup cooked white rice\n\t+ 1 cup mixed greens\n\n**Tips and Swaps:**\n\n* Drink water instead of sugary drinks to save money and calories.\n* Buy in bulk and plan meals around staples like oats, rice, beans, and canned goods.\n* Use herbs and spices to add flavor instead of relying on expensive sauces.\n* Shop for seasonal produce to get the best prices.\n* Consider shopping at discount stores or using cashback apps to stretch your budget.\n\n**Sample Grocery List:**\n\n* Oats (1 bag, $2)\n* Bananas (4-5, $1)\n* Peanut butter (1 jar, $2)\n* Jelly (1 jar, $1)\n* Whole wheat bread (1 loaf, $2)\n* Carrots (1 bunch, $0.60)\n* Apples (4-5, $2)\n* Almonds (1 bag, $5) (use sparingly or swap with cheaper nuts)\n* Black beans (1 can, $1)\n* Rice (1 bag, $1)\n* Mixed greens (1 bag, $1)\n\n**Remember:**\n\n* Losing weight too quickly is not healthy. Aim for a sustainable weight loss of 1-2 lbs per week.\n* Consult with a healthcare professional or registered dietitian before starting any new diet or exercise plan.\n* Be patient and consistent with your workout and diet plan. It may take some time to see results, but with dedication and hard work, you can reach your goal of losing 10 lbs.",
